ts of England well into the 17th century and was revived at the end of the 19th century to much more widespread use, while still retaining its popularity in Scotland. Since the 1960s, however, it has rather gone out of fashion in Britain."],"variants":[{"name":"Jannet","meanings":["Originally a diminutive of   Jane  , already in common use in the Middle English period. It remained in use in Scotland and in some parts of England well into the 17th century and was revived at the end of the 19th century to much more widespread use, while still retaining its popularity in Scotland. Since the 1960s, however, it has rather gone out of fashion in Britain."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Janet Maxwell was born about 1470, in Caerlaverock, Dumfriesshire, Scotland, her father, John Maxwell - Master Of Maxwell, was 41 and her mother, Janet Crichton, was 37. She married William Carlyle House of Torthorwald, Second Lord of Carlyle before 12 July 1487, in Dumfries, Dumfriesshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 2 daughters."},"et":{"about 1470–Deceased":"umbes 1470–Surnud","1450–1513":"1450–1513","1460–Male":"1460–Surnud","1463–Male":"1463–Surnud","1464–Male":"1464–Surnud","1470–Female":"1470–Surnud","1480–1560":"1480–1560","1485–1530":"1485–1530","1466–1525":"1466–1525","1492–1525":"1492–1525","1495–Female":"1495–Surnud","1501–1575":"1501–1575","1504–1564":"1504–1564","–1573":"–1573","1430–1484":"1430–1484","1434–Female":"1434–Surnud","about 1470":"umbes 1470","1484":"1484","1495":"1495","1560":"1560","1450":"1450","1460":"1460","1492":"1492","1470":"1470","1480":"1480","1525":"1525","1513":"1513","1501":"1501","1434":"1434","1466":"1466","1564":"1564","1575":"1575","1530":"1530","1464":"1464","1430":"1430","1573":"1573","1485":"1485","1463":"1463","1504":"1504","Caerlaverock, Dumfriesshire, Scotland":"Caerlaverock, Dumfriesshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"about 1470–Deceased":"noin 1470–Kuollut","1450–1513":"1450–1513","1460–Male":"1460–Kuollut","1463–M